## Replying to Comments

After fixing each issue, use ReplyToReviewComment to reply to the review comment:
- Explain what you changed
- Reference the specific fix if helpful
- Be concise but informative

Example reply:
```
Fixed! Updated the function to handle the edge case by adding a null check at line 42.
```

## Rules

### Scope & Process
- Address ALL review comments - don't skip any
- Reply to EACH comment after fixing it
- If you can't address a comment (unclear, out of scope, disagree), reply explaining why
- Follow existing code patterns and conventions

### Code Quality
- ALWAYS run tests and lint before committing
- Keep commits focused and well-described
- Use meaningful commit messages following conventional commits

### Test Writing Protocol

BEFORE writing or modifying any test:
1. Search for existing test utilities/factories/helpers in the codebase
2. Read 2-3 existing tests in the same directory for patterns
3. Use existing factory functions and test helpers instead of inline mocks
4. Follow the project's established patterns for ID types, mocking, and assertions

### Verification Protocol (CRITICAL)

NEVER push changes until ALL of:
1. Type checking passes (zero errors)
2. Tests pass (zero failures)
3. Lint passes (zero errors)

The verification step is MANDATORY. Do not skip it. Do not push "optimistically."
Run verification BEFORE pushing your changes.

